article.headline: Lehigh 102, Fairleigh Dickinson 62
article.story: BETHLEHEM, Pa. -- C.J. McCollum scored 23 points and Stefan Cvrkalj added a career-high 20 off the bench as Lehigh routed Fairleigh Dickinson 102-62 in a nonconference game Saturday night. After Fairleigh Dickinson scored the opening basket, the Mountain Hawks (6-2) got the next 23 points and led by as many as 33 before closing the first half with a 46-17 lead. McCollum scored 12 points in the half, when Lehigh shot 61.5 percent (16 of 26) to the Knights' 25 percent (5 of 20). The Mountain Hawks shot even better in the second half, when Cvrkalj scored 15 of his points, making 22 of 34 (64.7 percent). Gabe Knutson added 16 points for Lehigh, who earned coach Brett Reed his 100th win in his sixth season. At 100-65, he's the fastest in the Patriot League to reach that mark. Lonnie Robinson scored 21 points for the Knights (3-4).
